casebody.data:
Jan Marie VATER, Appellant,
v.
DIRECTOR OF REVENUE, State of Missouri, Respondent. WD 81223 Missouri Court of Appeals, Western District. ORDER FILED: February 26, 2019 Daniel J. Kennedy and Cameron H.J. Cooper, Independence, MO, and Jeffrey S. Eastman, Gladstone, MO, Attorneys for Appellant. Eric S. Schmitt, Attorney General, and James A. Chenault, III, and Morgan L. Brewington, Special Assistant Attorneys General, Jefferson City, MO, Attorneys for Respondent. Before Division Three: Mark D. Pfeiffer, Presiding Judge, and Lisa White Hardwick and Anthony Rex Gabbert, Judges

Order

Per Curiam:

Ms. Jan M. Vater appeals from the judgment of the Circuit Court of Jackson County, Missouri, upholding the Director of Revenue's suspension of Vater's driver's license under section 302.505.1 after her arrest for driving a motor vehicle while intoxicated. Because a published opinion would have no precedential value, a memorandum of law has been provided to the parties. The judgment is affirmed. Rule 84.16(b).
